1
00:00:18,280 --> 00:00:25,040
[2012]

2
00:01:00,380 --> 00:01:01,290
Jin...

3
00:01:07,560 --> 00:01:08,480
Stop packing.

4
00:01:08,789 --> 00:01:09,789
I'll do it for you.

5
00:01:10,150 --> 00:01:11,070
Okay.

6
00:01:41,350 --> 00:01:42,280
Are you okay?

7
00:01:44,150 --> 00:01:44,870
I'm fine.

8
00:01:45,430 --> 00:01:47,289
I just can't stand seeing Jin cry.

9
00:01:52,400 --> 00:01:53,920
Why did it have to be Chuan?

10
00:01:55,479 --> 00:01:56,150
What?

11
00:01:56,560 --> 00:01:58,560
So many people went on that mission,

12
00:01:58,640 --> 00:02:00,040
but only he died.

13
00:02:00,790 --> 00:02:02,640
I don't know what kind of grudge
they could've had against him—

14
00:02:02,640 --> 00:02:04,090
they stabbed him a dozen times

15
00:02:04,090 --> 00:02:05,890
and finished him off with a shot.

16
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:09,100
Drug dealers like that

17
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:10,600
will stop at nothing.

18
00:02:12,010 --> 00:02:13,400
But Chuan died.

19
00:02:15,310 --> 00:02:16,310
I was injured too.

20
00:02:21,110 --> 00:02:22,570
But you made it back alive.

21
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:27,460
What do you mean, Jiang Cheng?

22
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:29,400
What the hell are you saying?

23
00:02:29,470 --> 00:02:31,280
Would you only be satisfied
if I died too, huh?

24
00:02:31,280 --> 00:02:33,400
Chuan was your brother, but I'm not?

25
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:34,630
One SWAT officer wasn't enough for you?

26
00:02:34,630 --> 00:02:36,430
You need another body before you're happy?

27
00:02:36,430 --> 00:02:37,800
What the hell is wrong with you, Zhan Wei?

28
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:38,400
Is that what I meant?

29
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:39,660
Then what did you mean?

30
00:02:40,150 --> 00:02:40,800
What's going on?

31
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:42,240
Why are you guys fighting?

32
00:02:42,240 --> 00:02:42,970
Jiang Cheng,

33
00:02:43,310 --> 00:02:45,240
everyone's devastated
about our brother's death.

34
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:47,100
Don't think you're the only one
entitled to act out.

35
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:49,230
Who's "acting out"? Say that clearly!

36
00:02:49,470 --> 00:02:51,840
You went on the mission together
that day, right?

37
00:02:51,840 --> 00:02:53,280
You don't even know how he died,

38
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:54,520
and you still had the nerve to come back?

39
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:55,800
Why didn't you chase them?

40
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:57,079
I'm telling you—
if I had been there that day,

41
00:02:57,079 --> 00:02:58,680
I would never have let anyone get away.

42
00:02:58,680 --> 00:03:00,400
Yeah, yeah, you're the most capable!

43
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:02,210
From now on, you can be
the eldest brother! Count me out!

44
00:03:02,210 --> 00:03:03,590
I don't deserve to be your brother!

45
00:03:03,590 --> 00:03:04,910
Cheng didn't mean that, Wei!

46
00:03:04,910 --> 00:03:06,570
That's exactly what he meant!

47
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:10,600
You just wished
I were the one who died that day.

48
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:12,520
Chuan came back, and I died there;

49
00:03:12,520 --> 00:03:14,280
then you'd be satisfied, huh?

50
00:03:14,470 --> 00:03:15,570
What are you doing, Jiang Cheng?

51
00:03:15,570 --> 00:03:16,520
Can you talk like a normal person?

52
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:17,280
Can you?

53
00:03:17,310 --> 00:03:18,170
Stop fighting!

54
00:03:23,680 --> 00:03:24,590
Wei, Wei!

55
00:03:24,590 --> 00:03:25,450
Don't touch me!

56
00:03:25,910 --> 00:03:26,590
Jin!

57
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:29,120
Wei!

58
00:03:29,890 --> 00:03:38,700
[Tomb of Martyr Zhou Chuan]

59
00:03:31,720 --> 00:03:32,770
You know what?

60
00:03:33,540 --> 00:03:34,920
Jiang Cheng asked me,

61
00:03:35,540 --> 00:03:38,070
"You and Chuan
went on that mission together.

62
00:03:38,520 --> 00:03:41,110
How come he died and you came back alive?"

63
00:03:42,150 --> 00:03:43,520
He meant nothing by it,

64
00:03:44,030 --> 00:03:45,870
but it scared the hell out of me.

65
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:47,630
I was sweating all over.

66
00:03:58,750 --> 00:04:00,120
That was a warning.

67
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,460
I have to stop seeing them.

68
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:05,960
Staying away is the safest thing to do.

69
00:04:07,750 --> 00:04:09,080
Jiang Cheng is like you—

70
00:04:09,150 --> 00:04:11,430
he has to get to the bottom of everything.

71
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:14,190
I've learned my lesson.

72
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:17,850
I won't give you anything
to use against me again.

73
00:05:36,710 --> 00:05:42,430
[Sunsets Secrets Regrets]

74
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:45,070
[Episode 25]

75
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:47,830
Zhao Ping?

76
00:05:51,070 --> 00:05:52,130
Never heard of him.

77
00:05:57,710 --> 00:05:59,370
He knew my brother, actually.

78
00:06:00,630 --> 00:06:02,560
Your brother was the top sniper.

79
00:06:02,940 --> 00:06:05,140
It's not surprising if anyone knew him.

80
00:06:05,360 --> 00:06:06,070
True.

81
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:10,830
During the 8/17 Case,

82
00:06:11,630 --> 00:06:12,560
he was there too.

83
00:06:14,190 --> 00:06:15,520
Then I must have met him,

84
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:17,480
but the name doesn't ring a bell.

85
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:19,410
A lot of people were there that day.

86
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:21,240
Four squadrons sent people.

87
00:06:21,240 --> 00:06:22,310
And everyone wore headgear.

88
00:06:22,310 --> 00:06:23,360
Even if I saw him,

89
00:06:23,390 --> 00:06:25,990
I probably couldn't match
his face to his name.

90
00:06:26,190 --> 00:06:27,000
What?

91
00:06:27,040 --> 00:06:28,430
Want me to look him up for you?

92
00:06:28,430 --> 00:06:29,120
No need.

93
00:06:29,950 --> 00:06:30,800
He's dead.

94
00:06:31,070 --> 00:06:31,950
Dead?

95
00:06:32,270 --> 00:06:32,870
Suicide.

96
00:06:38,380 --> 00:06:38,909
Alright,

97
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:39,800
I'm full.

98
00:06:40,970 --> 00:06:42,010
What's the rush?

99
00:06:42,100 --> 00:06:43,560
Finish this before you go.

100
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:44,530
I'll head back first.

101
00:06:44,530 --> 00:06:46,130
You should go back early too.

102
00:06:46,250 --> 00:06:47,920
Your wife is recovering from childbirth.

103
00:06:47,920 --> 00:06:49,310
You should take good care of her.

104
00:06:49,310 --> 00:06:50,820
We have a confinement nanny.

105
00:06:50,820 --> 00:06:51,460
It's fine.

106
00:06:51,670 --> 00:06:52,750
She just had a baby.

107
00:06:52,900 --> 00:06:54,140
You need to pay more attention to her.

108
00:06:54,140 --> 00:06:56,670
Otherwise, she might develop
postpartum depression.

109
00:06:56,670 --> 00:06:57,310
Got it.

110
00:06:57,870 --> 00:06:58,930
I'll get going then, Wei.

111
00:06:58,930 --> 00:06:59,520
Okay.

112
00:06:59,580 --> 00:07:00,580
See you at my baby's one-month party
the day after tomorrow.

113
00:07:00,580 --> 00:07:01,140
Okay.

114
00:07:15,230 --> 00:07:16,580
Zhao Ping is his friend,

115
00:07:16,820 --> 00:07:19,080
but he seems very resistant to Zhao Ping.

116
00:07:19,190 --> 00:07:19,990
You're right.

117
00:07:20,190 --> 00:07:21,430
Their physical distance is close—

118
00:07:21,430 --> 00:07:23,380
the kind of distance
you'd see between acquaintances

119
00:07:23,380 --> 00:07:24,070
or friends.

120
00:07:24,140 --> 00:07:25,340
Do you know Zhao Ping?

121
00:07:26,260 --> 00:07:27,320
Never heard of him.

122
00:07:28,830 --> 00:07:30,630
His left foot is angled outward,

123
00:07:31,500 --> 00:07:32,670
and he's in a defensive stance.

124
00:07:32,670 --> 00:07:34,730
He's looking for an opening to leave.

125
00:07:39,020 --> 00:07:40,190
You scared the hell out of me.

126
00:07:40,190 --> 00:07:41,260
Did I scare you?

127
00:07:41,260 --> 00:07:42,110
Wei.

128
00:07:42,990 --> 00:07:43,990
Take these back.

129
00:07:44,260 --> 00:07:45,500
If Director Wang can eat them,

130
00:07:45,500 --> 00:07:46,350
give them to him.

131
00:07:46,350 --> 00:07:47,060
If not,

132
00:07:47,090 --> 00:07:48,140
keep them for yourself.

133
00:07:48,140 --> 00:07:48,550
Here.

134
00:07:48,550 --> 00:07:49,140
Okay.

135
00:08:00,900 --> 00:08:01,580
Are you crazy?

136
00:08:01,580 --> 00:08:03,040
Watch where you're going!

137
00:08:05,940 --> 00:08:07,230
You're on a road.

138
00:08:08,020 --> 00:08:09,150
You got a death wish?

139
00:08:10,750 --> 00:08:12,350
Good thing you're here, Wei.

140
00:08:12,840 --> 00:08:14,100
What's wrong with you?

141
00:08:14,110 --> 00:08:15,460
You're completely out of it.

142
00:08:15,460 --> 00:08:16,590
Let me walk you back.

143
00:08:17,110 --> 00:08:17,750
No need.

144
00:08:17,900 --> 00:08:19,160
I can go back by myself.

145
00:08:19,430 --> 00:08:20,480
Walk slowly.

146
00:08:20,550 --> 00:08:21,460
Look both ways.

147
00:08:22,900 --> 00:08:24,260
I'm not a kid anymore.

148
00:08:30,820 --> 00:08:31,580
Let me.

149
00:08:35,299 --> 00:08:36,150
Be careful now.

150
00:08:36,150 --> 00:08:36,820
Okay.

151
00:08:36,980 --> 00:08:38,510
Go ahead. I'll watch you go.

152
00:08:45,510 --> 00:08:47,240
Be careful! Watch out for cars!

153
00:09:23,670 --> 00:09:24,790
It's me.

154
00:09:25,580 --> 00:09:27,740
They're starting to suspect me.

155
00:09:28,510 --> 00:09:30,100
This is all your fault!

156
00:09:30,250 --> 00:09:34,980
[Yongchuan Police Station]

157
00:09:35,620 --> 00:09:37,310
Mom, you don't need to be this nervous.

158
00:09:37,310 --> 00:09:38,390
Just a reminder.

159
00:09:39,550 --> 00:09:40,670
Just stay safe

160
00:09:40,740 --> 00:09:42,940
and try not to go to remote places, okay?

161
00:09:44,310 --> 00:09:45,150
I know.

162
00:09:46,670 --> 00:09:47,340
Bye.

163
00:10:19,700 --> 00:10:20,670
You finished?

164
00:10:25,740 --> 00:10:26,670
How did it go?

165
00:10:27,580 --> 00:10:28,910
Did he tell everything?

166
00:10:31,190 --> 00:10:32,070
It was him.

167
00:10:34,910 --> 00:10:36,220
He's seen Qi Yan?

168
00:10:40,820 --> 00:10:42,220
And there's a middleman.

169
00:10:42,700 --> 00:10:43,960
We're looking into it,

170
00:10:44,740 --> 00:10:46,470
but we don't have enough leads.

171
00:10:47,070 --> 00:10:48,930
It won't be easy to track him down.

172
00:10:56,980 --> 00:10:58,980
If he'd really wanted to kill Prof,

173
00:10:59,620 --> 00:11:01,270
he wouldn't have done it

174
00:11:01,550 --> 00:11:03,100
at the Provincial Bureau's dorms.

175
00:11:03,100 --> 00:11:04,220
So brazenly...

176
00:11:05,030 --> 00:11:06,430
It's more like a warning.

177
00:11:07,840 --> 00:11:09,620
Give your dad and Mrs. Fang a call

178
00:11:09,620 --> 00:11:11,410
and tell them to be careful.

179
00:11:15,700 --> 00:11:16,900
Then wait for me here.

180
00:11:27,310 --> 00:11:28,030
These...

181
00:11:28,360 --> 00:11:29,420
Wei gave them to me.

182
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:40,270
Dad, it's me.

183
00:11:41,910 --> 00:11:43,310
How have you been lately?

184
00:11:50,100 --> 00:11:52,030
Knowing the criminal's
personality weaknesses

185
00:11:52,030 --> 00:11:53,830
means knowing how to enrage him.

186
00:11:53,860 --> 00:11:55,190
I just threw out bait,

187
00:11:55,790 --> 00:11:56,790
and he took it.

188
00:11:56,980 --> 00:11:57,790
What bait?

189
00:12:00,370 --> 00:12:01,020
Me.

190
00:13:10,310 --> 00:13:11,310
Hansheng.

191
00:13:16,520 --> 00:13:17,520
I love you.

192
00:13:22,900 --> 00:13:25,030
[Wei, are you free tomorrow?]

193
00:13:25,120 --> 00:13:28,040
[Yeah, what do you have in mind?]

194
00:13:51,720 --> 00:13:52,650
I'm heading out.

195
00:13:53,120 --> 00:13:53,760
Now?

196
00:13:55,370 --> 00:13:56,740
What time are you meeting Wei?

197
00:13:56,740 --> 00:13:58,000
We're meeting at noon.

198
00:13:58,430 --> 00:14:00,310
But I want to go pick up a gift first

199
00:14:00,470 --> 00:14:01,670
for my little nephew.

200
00:14:02,100 --> 00:14:04,070
Maybe a bracelet or a necklace.

201
00:14:04,150 --> 00:14:05,410
I haven't decided yet.

202
00:14:06,290 --> 00:14:08,030
Are you sure you don't want me to come?

203
00:14:08,030 --> 00:14:08,670
It's okay.

204
00:14:10,040 --> 00:14:11,270
I'll just pop over to his place

205
00:14:11,270 --> 00:14:12,130
to see the baby.

206
00:14:12,450 --> 00:14:13,650
You go visit Mr. Wang.

207
00:14:16,430 --> 00:14:17,850
Remember to have breakfast.

208
00:14:17,850 --> 00:14:18,280
Okay.

209
00:14:18,840 --> 00:14:19,700
Have you eaten?

210
00:14:22,290 --> 00:14:23,220
I'm heading out.

211
00:14:30,520 --> 00:14:31,920
It's getting cold today.

212
00:14:32,100 --> 00:14:33,230
Can I wear your coat?

213
00:14:33,400 --> 00:14:34,000
Of course.

214
00:14:40,110 --> 00:14:40,570
Come on.

215
00:15:04,550 --> 00:15:05,270
I'm off.

216
00:15:06,340 --> 00:15:07,600
Take care of yourself.

217
00:15:13,890 --> 00:15:14,820
Remember to eat.

218
00:15:18,340 --> 00:15:18,850
Bye.

219
00:16:06,030 --> 00:16:06,620
These...

220
00:16:06,940 --> 00:16:08,000
Wei gave them to me.

221
00:16:08,430 --> 00:16:11,000
Wei works in the Information Department
at the Provincial Bureau.

222
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:11,930
Nice to meet you.

223
00:16:12,030 --> 00:16:12,760
I'm Zhan Wei.

224
00:16:14,040 --> 00:16:15,620
Who's that person next to him?

225
00:16:15,620 --> 00:16:16,550
Hard to make out.

226
00:16:17,170 --> 00:16:17,890
Too blurry.

227
00:16:18,840 --> 00:16:20,500
We'll have to verify it again.

228
00:16:34,030 --> 00:16:35,030
Professor Jiang.

229
00:16:38,790 --> 00:16:39,430
Wei.

230
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:41,840
Jin.

231
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:44,030
For my nephew.

232
00:16:44,060 --> 00:16:45,230
You just bought it, didn't you?

233
00:16:45,230 --> 00:16:47,090
No wonder you wanted to meet here.

234
00:16:47,320 --> 00:16:47,910
Thanks.

235
00:16:50,960 --> 00:16:51,760
What's wrong?

236
00:16:52,030 --> 00:16:54,760
That's obviously
your husband's coat, isn't it?

237
00:16:54,790 --> 00:16:55,910
If your brother were here,

238
00:16:55,910 --> 00:16:58,710
he'd say
you're dressing inappropriately again.

239
00:16:59,840 --> 00:17:00,770
Let's go. Get in.

240
00:17:12,660 --> 00:17:14,130
Why the sudden decision to leave today?

241
00:17:14,130 --> 00:17:15,520
Can't you stay one more day?

242
00:17:15,520 --> 00:17:17,069
Besides, today is Saturday.

243
00:17:17,069 --> 00:17:17,859
There's a mission at the station.

244
00:17:17,859 --> 00:17:19,520
They need me back by tomorrow.

245
00:17:20,250 --> 00:17:22,530
Seems our Jin is the backbone of the team.

246
00:17:22,560 --> 00:17:23,579
They can't manage without you.

247
00:17:23,579 --> 00:17:25,980
It's mostly because we're short-staffed.

248
00:17:33,140 --> 00:17:34,870
Slow down. Don't get too close.

249
00:17:43,630 --> 00:17:44,470
Qian,

250
00:17:44,490 --> 00:17:45,520
maintain a safe distance.

251
00:17:45,520 --> 00:17:45,990
Okay,

252
00:17:46,250 --> 00:17:46,980
understood.

253
00:17:59,310 --> 00:18:00,310
Is your place far?

254
00:18:00,880 --> 00:18:02,010
It's a bit of a drive.

255
00:18:02,030 --> 00:18:03,960
Why else would I come to pick you up?

256
00:18:04,620 --> 00:18:06,480
You can't make it
to my baby's one-month party,

257
00:18:06,480 --> 00:18:08,280
so you're making a special trip.

258
00:18:08,790 --> 00:18:10,310
You're a pretty good aunt.

259
00:18:11,860 --> 00:18:13,520
Then tell me, how much should I

260
00:18:13,930 --> 00:18:15,750
put in the red envelope as his aunt?

261
00:18:15,750 --> 00:18:17,100
We don't accept money.

262
00:18:17,130 --> 00:18:18,590
You don't need to give one.

263
00:18:18,950 --> 00:18:19,750
Why so formal?

264
00:18:19,750 --> 00:18:21,460
I've already withdrawn the cash.

265
00:18:21,460 --> 00:18:22,940
We're not allowed to accept any now.

266
00:18:22,940 --> 00:18:24,700
It might look like bribery.

267
00:18:25,380 --> 00:18:26,420
Your presence is enough.

268
00:18:26,420 --> 00:18:28,480
Besides, you already brought a gift.

269
00:18:28,600 --> 00:18:31,380
Actually, we weren't supposed to
accept gifts either.

270
00:18:31,380 --> 00:18:32,910
So strict even with family?

271
00:18:33,360 --> 00:18:34,320
We have to be.

272
00:18:34,990 --> 00:18:36,870
It's a matter of principle.

273
00:18:37,550 --> 00:18:38,660
And you're

274
00:18:39,100 --> 00:18:41,430
still hosting the party at Nanshan Manor?

275
00:18:41,470 --> 00:18:43,800
Just the name sounds pretty extravagant.

276
00:18:44,030 --> 00:18:46,430
Aren't you afraid of
what people might say?

277
00:18:46,900 --> 00:18:48,300
That place is beautiful.

278
00:18:48,700 --> 00:18:49,750
My wife likes it.

279
00:18:53,750 --> 00:18:55,190
After we're done at my place,

280
00:18:55,190 --> 00:18:57,760
I'll take you over to have a look.
How about that?

281
00:18:57,760 --> 00:18:59,560
What time is your train tonight?

282
00:19:07,100 --> 00:19:07,550
Jin?

283
00:19:11,140 --> 00:19:12,070
Half past eight.

284
00:19:13,470 --> 00:19:15,000
Then we have plenty of time.

285
00:19:20,900 --> 00:19:21,900
Professor Jiang,

286
00:19:22,180 --> 00:19:23,230
has Bai Yang arrived?

287
00:19:23,230 --> 00:19:23,830
He's here.

288
00:19:24,380 --> 00:19:24,980
Chief Tan,

289
00:19:25,470 --> 00:19:26,670
what's going on here?

290
00:19:26,740 --> 00:19:27,740
Where is Zhou Jin?

291
00:19:28,350 --> 00:19:29,150
Zhou Jin is...

292
00:19:29,910 --> 00:19:32,170
currently in the middle of an operation.

293
00:19:32,460 --> 00:19:33,720
Just hear me out first.

294
00:19:34,040 --> 00:19:35,900
Zhou Jin reported to me last night

295
00:19:36,510 --> 00:19:37,370
that she's made

296
00:19:37,660 --> 00:19:39,140
a major discovery in Jingzhou.

297
00:19:39,140 --> 00:19:39,950
However,

298
00:19:40,230 --> 00:19:41,790
she hasn't found any solid evidence yet.

299
00:19:41,790 --> 00:19:43,100
So she wants to use

300
00:19:43,310 --> 00:19:44,980
her personal friendship with the suspect

301
00:19:44,980 --> 00:19:46,380
to gather information

302
00:19:46,460 --> 00:19:47,940
and confirm

303
00:19:48,030 --> 00:19:49,030
whether her initial deduction

304
00:19:49,030 --> 00:19:49,820
is correct.

305
00:19:50,420 --> 00:19:51,310
This suspect

306
00:19:51,550 --> 00:19:53,420
is Zhan Wei from the Provincial Bureau's
Information Department?

307
00:19:53,420 --> 00:19:54,050
Yes.

308
00:19:54,180 --> 00:19:55,100
Zhou Jin suspects that he's

309
00:19:55,100 --> 00:19:56,790
connected to her brother's death.

310
00:19:56,790 --> 00:19:57,650
And may even be,

311
00:19:58,420 --> 00:19:59,580
just like Zhao Ping,

312
00:20:00,240 --> 00:20:01,480
one of Qi Yan's men.

313
00:20:02,790 --> 00:20:03,990
Zhan Wei and Zhao Ping

314
00:20:04,230 --> 00:20:06,090
joined SWAT around the same time,

315
00:20:06,420 --> 00:20:07,940
so they must know each other.

316
00:20:07,940 --> 00:20:10,280
But Zhan Wei has been
adamantly denying it,

317
00:20:10,280 --> 00:20:12,280
which makes him highly suspicious.

318
00:20:12,990 --> 00:20:13,820
Listen,

319
00:20:14,130 --> 00:20:15,420
I went to the SWAT team

320
00:20:15,510 --> 00:20:17,130
and checked the deployment roster

321
00:20:17,130 --> 00:20:18,620
for the 8/17 Case.

322
00:20:18,790 --> 00:20:20,050
There were 40 in total.

323
00:20:20,270 --> 00:20:20,950
Zhou Chuan,

324
00:20:21,560 --> 00:20:22,170
Zhan Wei,

325
00:20:22,800 --> 00:20:23,530
and Zhao Ping

326
00:20:23,900 --> 00:20:25,030
were all on the list.

327
00:20:25,510 --> 00:20:26,310
To be honest,

328
00:20:26,620 --> 00:20:28,510
if it weren't for what Zhao Ping said

329
00:20:28,510 --> 00:20:29,990
before he jumped off the building,

330
00:20:29,990 --> 00:20:31,950
no one would've thought to look into this.

331
00:20:31,950 --> 00:20:33,750
How is Zhou Jin going to
get information out of him?

332
00:20:33,750 --> 00:20:35,140
If Zhan Wei really works for Qi Yan,

333
00:20:35,140 --> 00:20:36,750
she's in great danger right now!

334
00:20:36,750 --> 00:20:37,350
Chief Tan,

335
00:20:37,480 --> 00:20:39,130
how far has this mission progressed?

336
00:20:39,130 --> 00:20:40,750
Can we suspend it immediately?

337
00:20:40,750 --> 00:20:41,950
They've already met.

338
00:20:47,960 --> 00:20:48,960
Professor Jiang.

339
00:20:51,820 --> 00:20:52,270
Yes.

340
00:20:52,690 --> 00:20:53,890
Don't panic yet.

341
00:20:54,170 --> 00:20:55,910
Zhou Jin was afraid that if you knew,

342
00:20:55,910 --> 00:20:56,770
you would worry

343
00:20:56,800 --> 00:20:58,230
and refuse to let her go through with it.

344
00:20:58,230 --> 00:20:59,540
So before the operation,

345
00:20:59,540 --> 00:21:01,200
she kept some things from you.

346
00:21:02,340 --> 00:21:02,910
But

347
00:21:02,950 --> 00:21:04,270
objectively speaking,

348
00:21:04,270 --> 00:21:05,820
Qi Yan has been off the grid

349
00:21:06,230 --> 00:21:07,560
for quite some time now.

350
00:21:07,690 --> 00:21:09,370
We need a breakthrough.

351
00:21:10,030 --> 00:21:10,830
I understand.

352
00:21:11,750 --> 00:21:12,270
Also,

353
00:21:12,450 --> 00:21:13,520
Zhou Jin asked me

354
00:21:13,580 --> 00:21:14,840
to tell you something.

355
00:21:16,340 --> 00:21:16,950
What is it?

356
00:21:17,570 --> 00:21:18,500
She said only you

357
00:21:19,540 --> 00:21:20,780
can always find her.

358
00:21:24,400 --> 00:21:25,200
I understand.

359
00:21:26,890 --> 00:21:28,290
I'll cooperate with her.

360
00:21:28,340 --> 00:21:28,860
Good.

361
00:21:28,990 --> 00:21:30,360
I sent Bai Yang

362
00:21:30,490 --> 00:21:32,350
to provide you with technical support.

363
00:21:32,350 --> 00:21:33,120
At the scene,

364
00:21:33,200 --> 00:21:34,540
Wan has got things covered.

365
00:21:34,540 --> 00:21:35,430
In short,

366
00:21:35,450 --> 00:21:37,610
everything is under control.

367
00:21:37,700 --> 00:21:38,800
You don't need to worry too much.

368
00:21:38,800 --> 00:21:39,790
All we need to do

369
00:21:39,830 --> 00:21:42,160
is keep close tabs on Zhou Jin's progress.

370
00:21:42,660 --> 00:21:43,140
Also,

371
00:21:43,480 --> 00:21:45,410
I'm on my way to Jingzhou right now.

372
00:21:46,750 --> 00:21:47,270
Okay.

373
00:22:00,340 --> 00:22:01,340
Professor Jiang,

374
00:22:01,480 --> 00:22:03,140
this is Mr. Wan and the others.

375
00:22:06,820 --> 00:22:07,760
Zhou Jin is here.

376
00:22:32,650 --> 00:22:34,510
Is it completely jammed up ahead?

377
00:22:36,490 --> 00:22:38,620
We've hit the usual traffic jam again.

378
00:22:40,200 --> 00:22:42,400
This is the way out of the city, isn't it?

379
00:22:44,840 --> 00:22:46,640
Taking the outer ring is faster.

380
00:22:46,640 --> 00:22:47,690
It's the weekend.

381
00:22:47,710 --> 00:22:49,570
Traffic in the city is even worse.

382
00:22:57,470 --> 00:22:58,730
Don't bother looking.

383
00:22:59,380 --> 00:23:00,310
There's

384
00:23:01,340 --> 00:23:02,630
no signal in my car.

385
00:23:06,880 --> 00:23:08,680
Where exactly are you taking me?

386
00:23:15,290 --> 00:23:17,150
We don't have solid evidence yet,

387
00:23:17,790 --> 00:23:19,280
but we need to ask Chief Liang

388
00:23:19,280 --> 00:23:21,140
to keep some officers on standby.

389
00:23:21,470 --> 00:23:22,820
We might need them very soon.

390
00:23:22,820 --> 00:23:23,180
Okay.

391
00:23:23,420 --> 00:23:24,350
I'll contact him right away.

392
00:23:24,350 --> 00:23:24,820
Okay.

393
00:23:27,670 --> 00:23:28,870
Mr. Wan, Mr. Wan,

394
00:23:28,890 --> 00:23:30,090
don't tail them too closely.

395
00:23:30,090 --> 00:23:31,090
If you lose them,

396
00:23:31,110 --> 00:23:33,340
I'll give you their real-time location.

397
00:23:33,340 --> 00:23:34,420
Okay, copy that.

398
00:23:34,920 --> 00:23:36,520
Don't tail them too closely.

399
00:23:40,130 --> 00:23:41,660
Didn't you ask me yesterday

400
00:23:42,580 --> 00:23:43,660
if I knew Zhao Ping?

401
00:23:45,030 --> 00:23:46,290
I remembered it later.

402
00:23:46,620 --> 00:23:47,480
Yes, I knew him.

403
00:23:49,340 --> 00:23:50,200
Were you close?

404
00:23:50,580 --> 00:23:51,420
Sort of.

405
00:23:52,310 --> 00:23:54,110
When he jumped off the building,

406
00:23:54,330 --> 00:23:55,310
you were there?

407
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:03,030
When Zhao Ping died,

408
00:24:03,660 --> 00:24:05,420
did he say something to you?

409
00:24:07,800 --> 00:24:10,600
You've been suspecting me all along,
haven't you?

410
00:24:14,420 --> 00:24:15,680
Suspected you of what?

411
00:24:16,820 --> 00:24:18,870
No need to keep up the act, Jin.

412
00:24:19,620 --> 00:24:22,510
The fact that you managed to
trace it to me is impressive enough.

413
00:24:22,510 --> 00:24:24,400
But I knew Zhao Ping too well.

414
00:24:24,780 --> 00:24:26,490
That guy was too soft-hearted.

415
00:24:26,490 --> 00:24:27,280
Useless.

416
00:24:27,820 --> 00:24:29,230
I reminded him many times

417
00:24:29,250 --> 00:24:31,090
to find a chance to get rid of you.

418
00:24:31,390 --> 00:24:32,450
But he wouldn't listen.

419
00:24:32,450 --> 00:24:33,750
If he had listened to me earlier,

420
00:24:33,750 --> 00:24:34,900
he'd have already been abroad

421
00:24:34,900 --> 00:24:37,310
with the money, starting a brand-new life.

422
00:24:37,310 --> 00:24:39,910
Why would he have needed to
jump off a building?

423
00:24:40,200 --> 00:24:41,200
So,

424
00:24:41,660 --> 00:24:42,950
those who don't listen

425
00:24:43,470 --> 00:24:45,140
never end up well.

426
00:24:46,680 --> 00:24:47,470
Jin,

427
00:24:48,350 --> 00:24:50,030
didn't I also advise you

428
00:24:51,480 --> 00:24:52,960
not to be so stubborn?

429
00:24:53,420 --> 00:24:54,820
You're a girl.

430
00:24:54,850 --> 00:24:56,500
Just get married properly,

431
00:24:56,900 --> 00:24:58,070
have a child or two,

432
00:24:58,070 --> 00:24:59,620
and live your life in peace—

433
00:24:59,650 --> 00:25:01,050
wouldn't that be better?

434
00:25:03,400 --> 00:25:06,240
But why are you just like

435
00:25:06,270 --> 00:25:07,620
your damn brother?

436
00:25:12,550 --> 00:25:13,680
So it really was you.

437
00:25:14,260 --> 00:25:15,950
He forced me!

438
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:19,140
Did I make

439
00:25:19,140 --> 00:25:21,230
some unforgivable mistake back then?

440
00:25:21,230 --> 00:25:22,100
No!

441
00:25:23,090 --> 00:25:25,220
You want to know what happened, right?

442
00:25:26,050 --> 00:25:26,900
I'll tell you.

443
00:25:27,550 --> 00:25:30,110
Back then, I was just leading
a routine police response

444
00:25:30,110 --> 00:25:32,470
and ran into some armed thugs brawling.

445
00:25:32,540 --> 00:25:33,890
Someone died,

446
00:25:33,910 --> 00:25:35,420
so the case became serious.

447
00:25:35,420 --> 00:25:36,030
Their boss

448
00:25:36,030 --> 00:25:37,650
wanted to invite me and my superior
to dinner,

449
00:25:37,650 --> 00:25:39,410
hoping to bury the case.

450
00:25:40,070 --> 00:25:42,610
My superior was too principled.
He wouldn't go.

451
00:25:42,610 --> 00:25:43,980
But that screwed me!

452
00:25:44,620 --> 00:25:47,420
My sick mother fell into their hands!

453
00:25:47,450 --> 00:25:49,420
Could I not go to that dinner?

454
00:25:50,020 --> 00:25:51,090
If it were you—

455
00:25:51,380 --> 00:25:52,400
for the sake of your brother—

456
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:53,730
could you have refused?

457
00:25:55,990 --> 00:25:57,630
They had the pull to smooth things over.

458
00:25:57,630 --> 00:25:59,220
What was I?

459
00:25:59,970 --> 00:26:02,030
Not only did they
leave my mother unharmed,

460
00:26:02,030 --> 00:26:04,510
but they also gave me 200,000
as hush money.

461
00:26:05,310 --> 00:26:07,200
I chose to keep my mouth shut.

462
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:09,240
200,000.

463
00:26:09,750 --> 00:26:12,710
I didn't make that much in a year.

464
00:26:15,030 --> 00:26:16,270
And for that money,

465
00:26:16,790 --> 00:26:17,990
you became like this?

466
00:26:18,860 --> 00:26:20,340
That's exactly

467
00:26:20,990 --> 00:26:23,780
what your brother said.

468
00:26:24,580 --> 00:26:27,140
That's why I hated Zhou Chuan so much.

469
00:26:27,710 --> 00:26:30,390
Easy for you to say
when it's not your neck on the line.

470
00:26:30,390 --> 00:26:32,580
You always stand on some moral high ground

471
00:26:32,580 --> 00:26:33,860
to judge others.

472
00:26:33,860 --> 00:26:35,530
What about me? What was I supposed to do?

473
00:26:35,530 --> 00:26:36,910
Go head-to-head with them,

474
00:26:36,910 --> 00:26:39,190
risking my job and my life

475
00:26:39,220 --> 00:26:40,460
to turn them in?

476
00:26:40,760 --> 00:26:41,520
Zhou Jin,

477
00:26:41,820 --> 00:26:43,820
I was just a rookie cop at the time!

478
00:26:43,840 --> 00:26:45,270
I chose to take the money
and keep my mouth shut!

479
00:26:45,270 --> 00:26:47,330
Is that really so hard to understand?

480
00:26:47,860 --> 00:26:51,180
[2012]

481
00:26:55,070 --> 00:26:56,950
So there's no room for discussion, huh?

482
00:26:56,950 --> 00:26:57,750
About what?

483
00:27:02,340 --> 00:27:03,820
I'll vouch for you

484
00:27:04,340 --> 00:27:05,910
and introduce you to them.

485
00:27:06,790 --> 00:27:07,820
I'll split

486
00:27:08,380 --> 00:27:09,510
that money with you.

487
00:27:12,950 --> 00:27:13,550
Wei,

488
00:27:14,470 --> 00:27:15,550
turn yourself in.

489
00:27:17,240 --> 00:27:17,990
Chuan,

490
00:27:18,930 --> 00:27:20,450
if you were in my shoes,

491
00:27:20,470 --> 00:27:22,180
you'd understand
that so much of what I've done

492
00:27:22,180 --> 00:27:23,860
was out of desperation!

493
00:27:23,920 --> 00:27:25,070
I can turn myself in.

494
00:27:25,070 --> 00:27:26,380
I can give up my job and even my life.

495
00:27:26,380 --> 00:27:27,860
But what about my family?

496
00:27:28,070 --> 00:27:29,070
Just because you refused

497
00:27:29,070 --> 00:27:30,750
to side with them,

498
00:27:30,790 --> 00:27:32,310
they came after your parents

499
00:27:32,310 --> 00:27:33,270
and your girlfriend—

500
00:27:33,270 --> 00:27:34,270
what would you do?

501
00:27:34,270 --> 00:27:35,550
If they dared lay a finger on my family,

502
00:27:35,550 --> 00:27:37,340
I'd arrest every last one of them!

503
00:27:37,340 --> 00:27:38,900
I'd have the courage
to go down fighting with them!

504
00:27:38,900 --> 00:27:39,580
Do you?

505
00:27:39,860 --> 00:27:40,990
Being a police officer,

506
00:27:40,990 --> 00:27:42,210
you need to have some real grit!

507
00:27:42,210 --> 00:27:42,840
Zhan Wei,

508
00:27:42,860 --> 00:27:43,820
don't forget

509
00:27:44,030 --> 00:27:45,550
you are a police officer!

510
00:28:05,620 --> 00:28:07,350
When you first joined the unit,

511
00:28:08,470 --> 00:28:10,600
there was a young officer in your squad

512
00:28:10,720 --> 00:28:13,200
who accidentally threw a grenade
into the trench.

513
00:28:13,200 --> 00:28:14,470
Without even thinking,

514
00:28:14,470 --> 00:28:16,270
you picked it up and threw it out.

515
00:28:16,710 --> 00:28:18,770
Then you threw yourself over the kid,

516
00:28:19,030 --> 00:28:20,950
shielding him with your own body.

517
00:28:21,170 --> 00:28:22,230
You saved his life.

518
00:28:22,580 --> 00:28:24,040
That's who you really are.

519
00:28:24,580 --> 00:28:25,270
I know

520
00:28:26,380 --> 00:28:29,440
you've worked harder than anyone else
all these years.

521
00:28:29,820 --> 00:28:31,270
You've endured a lot of hardship

522
00:28:31,270 --> 00:28:32,870
to get to where you are today.

523
00:28:36,700 --> 00:28:39,160
But you lost sight of
what you once stood for.

524
00:28:40,470 --> 00:28:42,420
I don't want those people
to ruin the Zhan Wei

525
00:28:42,420 --> 00:28:45,480
who once threw himself into harm's way
to save someone.

526
00:28:45,990 --> 00:28:47,270
I don't want those people

527
00:28:47,270 --> 00:28:48,820
to ruin my brother.

528
00:28:56,070 --> 00:28:56,790
Wei.

529
00:28:59,070 --> 00:29:00,270
There are some things

530
00:29:00,890 --> 00:29:02,950
you need to think through carefully.

531
00:29:05,450 --> 00:29:07,210
I hope the next time I see you,

532
00:29:08,620 --> 00:29:10,480
it'll be in the captain's office.

533
00:29:17,710 --> 00:29:18,380
Chuan.

534
00:29:43,820 --> 00:29:45,420
Jin's birthday is coming up.

535
00:29:47,700 --> 00:29:49,830
This is the present I prepared for her.

536
00:29:52,270 --> 00:29:53,000
Don't worry.

537
00:29:53,820 --> 00:29:55,620
I paid for it out of my own pocket.

538
00:29:56,710 --> 00:29:58,370
No matter what you think of me,

539
00:29:58,510 --> 00:29:59,470
you'll

540
00:30:00,790 --> 00:30:02,920
always be the ones I hold closest.

541
00:30:07,950 --> 00:30:09,280
As for taking the money,

542
00:30:09,480 --> 00:30:11,010
I'll come clean to the unit.

543
00:30:11,820 --> 00:30:12,470
Chuan,

544
00:30:13,180 --> 00:30:14,710
just give me a few more days.

545
00:30:16,580 --> 00:30:18,240
I want to go back to my hometown

546
00:30:19,370 --> 00:30:20,280
to see my mom.

547
00:30:27,770 --> 00:30:28,450
I know.

548
00:30:30,510 --> 00:30:32,370
I know it's hard to take this step.

549
00:30:35,140 --> 00:30:36,230
But you have to

550
00:30:37,030 --> 00:30:37,990
get through it.

551
00:30:40,750 --> 00:30:41,750
Don't let me down.

552
00:30:45,230 --> 00:30:47,310
When we come back
from the mission on the 17th,

553
00:30:47,310 --> 00:30:49,170
let's have a good drink together.

554
00:30:50,580 --> 00:30:51,790
You said it.

555
00:30:52,580 --> 00:30:53,340
It's a deal.

556
00:30:55,660 --> 00:30:56,520
A deal's a deal.

557
00:31:17,180 --> 00:31:17,820
It's me.

558
00:31:19,890 --> 00:31:22,450
I agree to all your previous demands.

559
00:31:24,180 --> 00:31:29,900
[August 17, 2012]

560
00:31:55,980 --> 00:31:56,550
Move in!

561
00:32:04,100 --> 00:32:04,790
Freeze!

562
00:32:06,340 --> 00:32:07,000
Don't move!

563
00:32:11,710 --> 00:32:12,710
Police!

564
00:32:13,230 --> 00:32:13,790
Freeze!

565
00:32:15,950 --> 00:32:17,070
Don't move!

566
00:32:20,580 --> 00:32:21,510
Police!

567
00:32:22,030 --> 00:32:22,660
Freeze!

568
00:32:25,330 --> 00:32:26,030
Freeze!

569
00:32:28,230 --> 00:32:29,020
No... Don't...

570
00:32:29,020 --> 00:32:29,420
Don't... Don't...

571
00:32:29,420 --> 00:32:29,750
Don't move!

572
00:32:29,750 --> 00:32:30,100
Please!

573
00:32:30,100 --> 00:32:31,740
It's my first time! I don't know anything!

574
00:32:31,740 --> 00:32:32,420
Zhao Ning?

575
00:32:32,580 --> 00:32:33,340
Is there anyone else here?

576
00:32:33,340 --> 00:32:34,810
Bring everyone you've caught over
to the vehicles!

577
00:32:34,810 --> 00:32:35,330
Sir,

578
00:32:35,380 --> 00:32:36,550
armed drug dealers spotted

579
00:32:36,550 --> 00:32:37,230
in the northwest corner!

580
00:32:37,230 --> 00:32:38,360
Requesting backup!

581
00:32:38,810 --> 00:32:40,660
What are you doing? You scared me!

582
00:32:40,660 --> 00:32:42,180
Can you do me a favor?

583
00:32:42,430 --> 00:32:43,060
What is it?

584
00:32:43,090 --> 00:32:43,660
Tell me.

585
00:32:43,820 --> 00:32:45,340
The guy with the beard in the car

586
00:32:45,340 --> 00:32:46,470
is my cousin.

587
00:32:47,440 --> 00:32:49,080
Could you put in a word with Captain Zhou

588
00:32:49,080 --> 00:32:49,800
for me?

589
00:32:50,140 --> 00:32:51,140
He's still a kid,

590
00:32:51,140 --> 00:32:52,340
just graduated from college.

591
00:32:52,340 --> 00:32:53,180
If he gets caught,

592
00:32:53,180 --> 00:32:54,340
his life is ruined.

593
00:32:54,340 --> 00:32:55,740
Are you crazy, Zhao Ping?

594
00:32:55,770 --> 00:32:56,660
You know

595
00:32:56,660 --> 00:32:57,990
what Zhou Chuan is like!

596
00:32:58,790 --> 00:33:00,020
I can't help you with this.

597
00:33:00,020 --> 00:33:00,310
Yes.

598
00:33:00,310 --> 00:33:02,240
I-I know what Captain Zhou is like.

599
00:33:02,450 --> 00:33:04,270
But he's the only son in his family!

600
00:33:04,270 --> 00:33:06,300
His parents are counting on him!

601
00:33:06,510 --> 00:33:07,630
If he goes to prison,

602
00:33:07,630 --> 00:33:08,630
it's really over—

603
00:33:08,660 --> 00:33:09,950
the whole family will be destroyed!

604
00:33:09,950 --> 00:33:11,790
So could you please help me talk to...

605
00:33:11,790 --> 00:33:12,860
Unless...

606
00:33:15,270 --> 00:33:16,870
you can draw Zhou Chuan away—

607
00:33:17,320 --> 00:33:18,720
the further, the better.

608
00:33:19,030 --> 00:33:20,760
I'll find a chance to let him go.

609
00:33:22,560 --> 00:33:23,030
Okay.

610
00:33:23,660 --> 00:33:24,340
Okay.

611
00:33:25,480 --> 00:33:26,080
Remember.

612
00:33:27,180 --> 00:33:29,140
Don't alert anyone.

613
00:33:30,550 --> 00:33:31,280
Understood.

614
00:33:37,710 --> 00:33:38,510
Captain Zhou!

615
00:33:38,860 --> 00:33:39,860
I noticed a place.

616
00:33:40,070 --> 00:33:41,100
Looks very suspicious.

617
00:33:41,100 --> 00:33:42,020
Do you want to go and take a look?

618
00:33:42,020 --> 00:33:42,750
Where is it?

619
00:33:42,750 --> 00:33:43,380
I'll take you there.

620
00:33:43,380 --> 00:33:43,910
Let's go.

621
00:33:56,500 --> 00:33:57,430
Is it here?

622
00:33:58,580 --> 00:33:58,990
It...

623
00:33:59,270 --> 00:34:00,380
it should be here.

624
00:34:02,950 --> 00:34:04,420
They were right here just now.

625
00:34:04,420 --> 00:34:05,150
Are you sure?

626
00:34:06,940 --> 00:34:08,020
Maybe it's ahead.

627
00:34:09,139 --> 00:34:10,330
If you really found something,

628
00:34:10,330 --> 00:34:11,929
you'll make a contribution.

629
00:34:25,070 --> 00:34:26,330
There's nothing here.

630
00:34:27,350 --> 00:34:28,150
Captain Zhou.

631
00:34:28,179 --> 00:34:28,909
Zhao Ping,

632
00:34:29,139 --> 00:34:30,940
do you have something to tell me?

633
00:34:31,139 --> 00:34:31,940
Captain Zhou.

634
00:34:32,100 --> 00:34:33,060
Actually, I...

635
00:34:57,150 --> 00:34:58,360
You hurt me.

636
00:35:17,370 --> 00:35:18,700
Your name is Zhou Chuan?

637
00:35:20,030 --> 00:35:20,990
Who are you?

638
00:35:21,900 --> 00:35:23,500
I have no grudge against you.

639
00:35:23,540 --> 00:35:24,870
I don't want to kill you.

640
00:35:25,430 --> 00:35:26,660
It's your brother

641
00:35:27,040 --> 00:35:28,100
who wants you dead.

642
00:35:29,470 --> 00:35:30,350
Sorry.

643
00:35:41,050 --> 00:35:41,740
Thank you.

644
00:35:47,630 --> 00:35:48,510
Zhan Wei,

645
00:35:49,150 --> 00:35:50,810
come out and collect the body!

646
00:36:04,160 --> 00:36:06,340
Do you know how I felt

647
00:36:06,370 --> 00:36:08,040
when Zhou Chuan died?

648
00:36:09,510 --> 00:36:11,510
The whole world went quiet,

649
00:36:12,400 --> 00:36:14,230
and my heart was at peace.

650
00:36:16,870 --> 00:36:17,660
Zhou Jin,

651
00:36:18,620 --> 00:36:20,220
don't be so naive.

652
00:36:20,880 --> 00:36:23,230
Let me tell you two final truths.

653
00:36:24,350 --> 00:36:25,220
First,

654
00:36:25,390 --> 00:36:27,260
those who can read the situation

655
00:36:27,470 --> 00:36:29,300
will never lose.

656
00:36:29,700 --> 00:36:31,100
Actually, just like you,

657
00:36:31,620 --> 00:36:33,100
I really hate Qi Yan.

658
00:36:33,470 --> 00:36:35,140
That man is a lunatic.

659
00:36:35,510 --> 00:36:37,700
That's why I kept encouraging you
to investigate,

660
00:36:37,700 --> 00:36:39,700
hoping you'd bring him down

661
00:36:39,700 --> 00:36:40,910
for me.

662
00:36:41,740 --> 00:36:42,780
I'd been

663
00:36:42,810 --> 00:36:44,470
looking into the two undercovers

664
00:36:44,470 --> 00:36:46,190
Yao Weihai planted
around Qi Yan five years ago.

665
00:36:46,190 --> 00:36:47,550
One was Meng Junfeng.

666
00:36:47,570 --> 00:36:49,770
Before I could find out about the other,

667
00:36:49,920 --> 00:36:51,950
Yao Weihai discovered
that the undercover files had been leaked

668
00:36:51,950 --> 00:36:54,390
and deleted everything.

669
00:36:55,030 --> 00:36:58,070
Yet Meng Junfeng wasn't exposed
until five years later.

670
00:36:58,070 --> 00:36:59,510
Do you know why?

671
00:37:00,260 --> 00:37:02,090
Because I protected him.

672
00:37:02,990 --> 00:37:06,700
It would've been ideal if the task force
could've taken down Qi Yan.

673
00:37:06,700 --> 00:37:08,100
But later, I heard

674
00:37:09,990 --> 00:37:11,780
that both Meng Junfeng and Yao Weihai

675
00:37:11,780 --> 00:37:13,950
were outwitted and killed by Qi Yan.

676
00:37:14,280 --> 00:37:15,800
Qi Yan was the winner.

677
00:37:15,830 --> 00:37:18,060
So I stand on the winner's side.

678
00:37:18,470 --> 00:37:20,870
That's what it means
to read the situation.

679
00:37:21,430 --> 00:37:22,830
And another truth—

680
00:37:23,300 --> 00:37:25,260
if you want to win to the very end,

681
00:37:25,700 --> 00:37:28,660
you have to be willing to risk it all.

682
00:37:34,580 --> 00:37:35,550
Jin...

683
00:37:37,840 --> 00:37:40,590
you shouldn't have gotten into my car.

684
00:38:04,430 --> 00:38:05,160
Hansheng...

685
00:38:21,660 --> 00:38:22,910
We finally meet.

686
00:38:25,700 --> 00:38:26,660
Officer Zhou.

687
00:38:27,890 --> 00:38:28,560
Bai Yang,

688
00:38:28,890 --> 00:38:29,830
what's going on ahead?

689
00:38:29,830 --> 00:38:30,830
We're stuck here.

690
00:38:32,660 --> 00:38:34,740
Looks like there's been a traffic accident
up ahead.

691
00:38:34,740 --> 00:38:36,270
I need to check the details.

692
00:38:36,620 --> 00:38:38,420
What about Zhou Jin and Zhan Wei?

693
00:38:40,000 --> 00:38:41,260
They're still moving.

694
00:38:41,290 --> 00:38:42,220
Okay. Copy that.

695
00:38:42,870 --> 00:38:43,550
It's Qi Yan.

696
00:38:44,020 --> 00:38:45,150
Qi Yan took the bait.

697
00:38:46,180 --> 00:38:48,550
For people like me
in the restaurant industry,

698
00:38:48,550 --> 00:38:49,220
we just

699
00:38:49,330 --> 00:38:50,670
can't stand messy tables.

700
00:38:50,670 --> 00:38:52,130
Drives me crazy, you know?

701
00:38:52,710 --> 00:38:54,370
Did Jin reply to your message?

702
00:38:57,350 --> 00:38:57,830
No.

703
00:38:59,100 --> 00:39:00,300
That's fine, I guess.

704
00:39:00,350 --> 00:39:01,070
We don't

705
00:39:01,070 --> 00:39:02,470
all have to give the same amount, right?

706
00:39:02,470 --> 00:39:04,000
As long as ours are the same.

707
00:39:04,590 --> 00:39:05,510
How could she go three hours

708
00:39:05,510 --> 00:39:06,910
without replying to you?

709
00:39:07,140 --> 00:39:07,950
Busy.

710
00:39:11,260 --> 00:39:12,830
You look restless.

711
00:39:12,940 --> 00:39:14,600
Do you need her for something?

712
00:39:14,870 --> 00:39:16,150
Didn't Jin go to Jingzhou

713
00:39:16,150 --> 00:39:17,280
to attend the party?

714
00:39:22,300 --> 00:39:23,180
Stop smoking.

715
00:39:23,810 --> 00:39:25,470
Start by not smoking indoors.

716
00:39:27,610 --> 00:39:28,220
How about this:

717
00:39:28,220 --> 00:39:29,350
give Jin a call.

718
00:39:30,690 --> 00:39:32,320
Call her and see if she picks up.

719
00:39:32,320 --> 00:39:32,920
Hurry.

720
00:39:41,950 --> 00:39:44,470
Hello. The number you dialed
is powered off.

721
00:39:46,550 --> 00:39:47,480
Her phone's off.

722
00:39:49,220 --> 00:39:50,480
Take me to the station.

723
00:39:51,890 --> 00:39:52,550
What station?

724
00:39:52,550 --> 00:39:53,350
You're not even on the force!

725
00:39:53,350 --> 00:39:54,300
Jin's station!

726
00:39:58,350 --> 00:39:59,610
All units, attention.

727
00:39:59,620 --> 00:40:00,430
The hostage is

728
00:40:00,630 --> 00:40:02,430
Zhou Jin, an investigator
from Haizhou City

729
00:40:02,430 --> 00:40:03,300
Nancheng Branch.

730
00:40:03,300 --> 00:40:04,700
The suspect is Qi Yan,

731
00:40:05,100 --> 00:40:05,910
the prime suspect in the 8/17 Case,

732
00:40:05,910 --> 00:40:06,600
the Huaiguang Case,

733
00:40:06,600 --> 00:40:08,130
and the Jingang Wharf Case.

734
00:40:08,140 --> 00:40:09,260
The suspect is extremely dangerous,

735
00:40:09,260 --> 00:40:10,300
armed with firearms,

736
00:40:10,300 --> 00:40:12,830
and shows clear hostility
toward the police.

737
00:40:20,110 --> 00:40:22,310
There's an intersection
about 500 meters ahead,

738
00:40:22,310 --> 00:40:23,910
heading toward the suburbs.

739
00:40:28,530 --> 00:40:29,210
Umm...

740
00:40:29,400 --> 00:40:30,530
Professor Jiang...

741
00:40:31,000 --> 00:40:33,930
T-There's a speed limit on this road.
How about we...

742
00:40:34,320 --> 00:40:35,520
What's the distance?

743
00:40:37,580 --> 00:40:38,510
2.3 kilometers.

744
00:40:47,780 --> 00:40:48,450
No!

745
00:40:49,140 --> 00:40:50,270
He's toying with us.

746
00:40:50,510 --> 00:40:52,240
He's headed back into the city.

747
00:41:00,390 --> 00:41:01,510
We're almost there.

748
00:41:01,510 --> 00:41:02,740
There's a small side road ahead.

749
00:41:02,740 --> 00:41:04,000
Turn left in 50 meters.

750
00:41:05,100 --> 00:41:07,300
There's an apartment complex
called Desi'en.

751
00:41:07,300 --> 00:41:08,350
Once past the side road,

752
00:41:08,350 --> 00:41:09,610
the traffic clears up.

753
00:41:12,640 --> 00:41:14,040
I've stayed here before.

754
00:41:36,390 --> 00:41:37,700
The tracking signals have now overlapped,

755
00:41:37,700 --> 00:41:38,550
but I can't determine

756
00:41:38,550 --> 00:41:40,430
exactly which room they're in,
Professor Jiang.

757
00:41:40,430 --> 00:41:41,430
Professor Jiang.

758
00:41:41,580 --> 00:41:42,560
Professor Jiang!

759
00:41:42,560 --> 00:41:43,660
They might have guns.

760
00:41:43,660 --> 00:41:44,660
I suggest we...
